        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-31T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-31T02:00:00-05:00" n="1229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1229">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Ward, Angus I.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-31T15:00:00+08:00">October 31, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 2—6:09 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>890. Items re Ward at Mukden appeared in Tientsin press October 30 similar to
                    those reported in Peiping telegram 1827, October 26.</p>
                <p>Some Chinese here privately express opinion present agitation against Ward is
                    build-up preparatory to “expelling” Ward and other members of ConGen staff from
                    Mukden as face-saving device.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
